<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-31T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="818" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d818">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/1035</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-31T18:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1374. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>, <persName>Smith</persName> [from War Trade
                            Board]:</p>
                        <p>No. 177. Embassy’s 1577, your No. 169, July 23, 11 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d818fn1">Not printed.</note> The Department has considered
                            wise to allow Cuban authorities to restrict call of Spanish steamers
                            bound from Cuba for Mexican ports and this has now been agreed to by
                            Cuban authorities. Can see no objections to arranging with Spanish
                            Transatlantic and Pinillos Lines to cease their calls to Mexican ports
                            and so soon as you have arranged please cable and we will instruct
                            connecting lines accordingly; also Cuban officials as to
                            transshipments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>